content.text:
In a conversation with Euroleague Basketball’s Javier Gancedo just before he and his team face Cedevita Olimpija Ljubljana in the EuroCup Eighthfinals, [Kevin Yebo](https://www.euroleaguebasketball.net/en/eurocup/players/kevin-yebo/013368/) of [NINERS Chemnitz](https://www.euroleaguebasketball.net/en/eurocup/teams/niners-chemnitz/nin/) doesn’t hesitate to define his team's mindset: “We have nothing to lose.” After a debut season marked by injuries, growth, and resilience, the forward believes the underdog role frees his team to bring its best energy to the playoffs.

&nbsp;

**Congratulations on a great season and on helping Chemnitz reach the EuroCup Playoffs in its first season in the competition.**

"I think it is a big achievement for the organization. It is our first year in the EuroCup, and the first time that we play a competition at such a high level like this, where every game counts, and also playing in the German League, so two competitions. But we had a lot of injury problems as well. I think that we still managed to make it to the EuroCup Playoffs in the first season of the organization shows the quality of this team. It was not perfect, but we found a way and I am really proud of that fact."

&nbsp;

**You had a long break now before this do-or-die playoff game. How was the break for you guys? Did you take time off?**

"I didn't take time off, to be honest. I played for the Ivory Coast national team. We played the World Cup qualifiers and had three games in four days. Before that, we had three days of a little training camp. I had two days off right after the last game of the German League. I enjoyed the sun for sure over there. I was at the beach with good food and played basketball as well. We won all three games, and now I'm back with the team here in Chemnitz. We will be ready for the playoff game. When I was not there, the guys had a good week of practice.

&nbsp;

**Let's talk about Cedevita then. They are a very experienced team and they play at home. What do you like about them, and how good is it to go to Ljubljana as the underdog?**

"I think it's a really good team. You can see a lot of videos, of course. But in the end, we try to get ready for this team. In the end, we have to go there and play away at their home court. We have to focus on bringing the right energy and the right mindset. That's the first thing we have to do. Go there with the right energy and don't focus on the opponents, bring our energy to the game and make sure that we do our thing. We will see in the game what we have to focus on."

